    • Method Detail

      • handle

        public void handle(java.lang.Throwable thrown)
        Has a hard coded error message that will be printed if it is either an out of memory error, or another type of error. This will send the thrown error stack trace to printwriter. In addition a string is created with copy of stack trace that will be printed in a new dialog.
        Parameters:
        thrown - the error being thrown.
